About 5 years ago I linked 100 rounds and fired it for the first time and it did well except occasionally the sear wouldn't catch and I had to wiggle the trigger a little before it fired the next round. Along the way I acquired an M2 tripod with pintle and T&E mechanism that I understand was used in Israel, it had a coat of ugly, thick sand colored paint. I can send a picture if interested. I also have a linker, a few hundred links, a trunion shield for using the metal links, one cloth belt and an Army manual.

The gun itself is in as new condition. Fired once and on display the rest of it's life. It was assembled by a company called Rapid Fire out of Ohio.
